Advice Generator App

Overview
The Advice Generator App fetches random pieces of advice from the Advice Slip API and displays them in a clean, responsive interface. Users can click a button to receive new advice, and the layout adapts to different screen sizes for a seamless experience on mobile and desktop devices.

Technologies Used
HTML: Structure and layout of the app.
CSS: Styling the app based on the provided style guide, ensuring responsiveness.
JavaScript: Handles asynchronous API requests and dynamically updates the UI.
Advice Slip API: Used to fetch random advice via a GET request.
Features

Responsive Design: The app adapts to different screen sizes, providing a mobile-first experience that scales to larger devices (up to 1440px).
API Integration: Uses fetch to retrieve advice from the API and display it.
User Interaction: Simple button for fetching new advice. Includes error handling in case of a failed API request.

Design
Color Scheme:
Background: Light Cyan
Button: Neon Green
Text: Grayish Blue
Typography:
Font: Manrope (weight 800)
Size: 28px for advice text
Layout: Mobile-first, with media queries to adjust layout for tablet and desktop screens.

Code Structure
HTML: Basic structure with a button to fetch advice and a div for displaying it.
CSS: External stylesheet styles.css that handles layout, styling, and responsiveness.
JavaScript: app.js handles API requests and updates the DOM with new advice.